<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> For instance, Druids and Necromancers are known for their versatility, with Necromancers being more powerful, and druids being more useful to the group.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Pulled the quote from Cass' Druid history post.  It seems to indicate that Verant saw Necros as the &quot;loner&quot; class, not Druids.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm in favor of upgrading Cleric soloability if group desirability of Druids is increased commensurately (The Grovers have supplied lots of ideas as to how this can be done without necessarily treading on CH).  I'm not opposed to other classes gaining new abilities, but not at the expense of attention to existing class issues.  <br>
